# Research the Front Backlog Shape

## Question

15,067 open conversations is a shape, not a number. Analyze read-only
via the joelclaw CLI / Front API surface — aggregates only, never
bodies: age distribution (how many touched in 24h / 7d / 30d / 90d /
older), inbox/tag breakdown, top senders by volume (domains ok, no
content), and how many are obviously terminal (newsletters,
notifications, bounced, auto-replies) vs plausibly-live threads.
Produce an asset with the numbers plus a staged burn-down proposal:
what a bulk-archive of the terminal cohorts would remove (recompute the
count per cohort), what a sane steady state looks like, and what
standing mechanism defends it. Also spec the time-boxed sweep windows
(24h/7d/30d) for the external-context digest's Front section — exact
fields the digest should render instead of the all-time total.
Proposals only; every bulk action waits on Joel.
